the spring roll, Tom Yum soup,

257
00:14:41,014 --> 00:14:45,452
-green papaya, and massaman curry?
-Yes.

258
00:14:45,518 --> 00:14:49,956
Tonight's dinner is in a red container
on the top right corner of the fridge.

259
00:14:50,023 --> 00:14:51,858
Goulash soup should be heated
for three minutes.

260
00:14:51,925 --> 00:14:53,693
Microwave Sauteed the foie gras
for a minute.

261
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,695
Please eat the salad as is.

262
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:00,700
So it's Hungarian cuisine? That's rare.

263
00:15:01,801 --> 00:15:04,971
So does that mean we can't
eat together again tonight?

264
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:09,976
I can't go home tonight again.
I will be home after tomorrow night.

265
00:15:11,244 --> 00:15:12,245
I see.

266
00:15:15,015 --> 00:15:17,083
What? An all-nighter?

267
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:21,321
I stayed at an internet cafe,
but I couldn't sleep with all the noise.

268
00:15:23,189 --> 00:15:26,559
Well Mika called me yesterday
to pick her up.

269
00:15:26,626 --> 00:15:30,864
So I drove to Shinjuku in the middle
of the night and drove her home.

270
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,299
Really?

271
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:39,239
Lately, I've been thinking
that I should have taken the kids.

272
00:15:40,140 --> 00:15:41,141
Morning.

273
00:15:41,207 --> 00:15:43,576
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

274
00:15:43,643 --> 00:15:46,746
Niwano spent the night
at an internet cafe last night.

275
00:15:47,013 --> 00:15:49,416
I rest at an internet cafe
once in a while too.

276
00:15:49,482 --> 00:15:51,017
-Really?
-Yes.

277
00:15:51,985 --> 00:15:53,787
I saw on TV the other day

278
00:15:53,853 --> 00:15:55,555
that there are about 15,000 people

279
00:15:55,622 --> 00:15:58,725
who spend the night
at an internet cafe in Tokyo.

280
00:15:58,792 --> 00:16:03,797
And 4,000 of them actually live there!

281
00:16:04,531 --> 00:16:06,833
Ah, the internet cafe refugees?

282
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:10,303
I also heard that a majority of them
are in their 30s and 40s.

283
00:16:10,370 --> 00:16:11,805
I thought they would be younger.

284
00:16:11,871 --> 00:16:14,207
How regrettable for a grown man.

285
00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:17,744
This property is completely barrier free.

286
00:16:18,078 --> 00:16:19,346
I would think it's perfect for you.

287
00:16:19,813 --> 00:16:21,681
Don't ridicule the elderly!

288
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:26,619
I do 50 squats every day!

289
00:16:27,687 --> 00:16:29,522
Steps won't bother me!

290
00:16:29,889 --> 00:16:34,594
Pardon me. What I meant was that
it would be helpful in the future.

291
00:16:35,628 --> 00:16:38,365
Yeah, sounds like an excuse.
Let's move on.

292
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:44,137
This property is popular
for its great view of Mount Fuji.

293
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:48,074
If it's that popular,
then why is it still available?

294
00:16:48,308 --> 00:16:50,443
It's quite expensive.

295
00:16:50,810 --> 00:16:54,981
A rich Chinese will buy about
ten properties with cash.

296
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:57,817
Next! Let's go to the next one!

297
00:16:58,518 --> 00:17:03,223
I looked all night, but I only found
two properties so far--

298
00:17:03,289 --> 00:17:06,126
Ah! You scared me!

299
00:17:06,526 --> 00:17:09,362
Ms. Kamiko, what are you scared of?

300
00:17:09,429 --> 00:17:10,430
Chief Sangenya?

301
00:17:10,864 --> 00:17:16,035
My name is Sangenya of
the Teiko Real Estate, Shinjuku office.

302
00:17:17,637 --> 00:17:19,406
Machi Sangenya?

303
00:17:19,973 --> 00:17:21,641
You have a long name.

304
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:25,478
Tomoe Kamiko, Machi Sangenya…

305
00:17:26,279 --> 00:17:28,014
It's just one character longer.

306
00:17:28,615 --> 00:17:32,552
Tomoe Kamiko, Machi Sangenya.
You're right. It's just one character.

307
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:37,390
Even if it's just one character,
it makes a huge difference!

308
00:17:37,991 --> 00:17:40,727
One year is a big difference
in age too, right?

309
00:17:41,194 --> 00:17:44,230
Are you single? Because you seem like
you're hard to get along with.

310
00:17:44,531 --> 00:17:45,532
I am married.

311
00:17:45,799 --> 00:17:48,368
Is that how your name got longer?

312
00:17:48,768 --> 00:17:51,538
Um no, Sangenya uses
her maiden name for work.

313
00:17:52,205 --> 00:17:55,108
Ah, with that face of yours,

314
00:17:55,175 --> 00:17:59,746
you must be popular with men,
and that's why you're so stuck up.

315
00:18:00,146 --> 00:18:03,516
You might be trying to steal
Niwano's clients from him,

316
00:18:03,917 --> 00:18:07,854
but I'm not a guy,
so I won't be fooled by you.

317
00:18:08,254 --> 00:18:10,623
I've never been popular with men.

318
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:14,761
Even with my husband,
I proposed to him first.

319
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:18,798
You got him because you are beautiful.

320
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:21,668
Eventually, everyone will be gone.

321
00:18:21,734 --> 00:18:26,306
Even beautiful women become old hags.
Everyone will be gone then.

322
00:18:26,372 --> 00:18:31,711
It will get so lonely.
It will get very, very lonely.

323
00:18:31,778 --> 00:18:34,113
Very, very lonely!

324
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:37,250
Ms. Kamiko, I will sell you a house.

325
00:18:38,151 --> 00:18:40,720
She's not listening to what I'm saying.

326
00:18:41,488 --> 00:18:43,089
She does tend to do that.

327
00:18:43,723 --> 00:18:45,825
Please look forward to it.

328
00:18:46,926 --> 00:18:49,395
Let's leave this beauty
to find me a house.

329
00:18:49,462 --> 00:18:52,298
Niwano, let's go have a snack!

330
00:18:52,866 --> 00:18:55,869
A snack? I'm not so fond of sweets.

331
00:18:57,437 --> 00:18:59,072
Thank you for waiting.

332
00:18:59,672 --> 00:19:01,007
Eat it.

333
00:19:01,241 --> 00:19:02,242
Thank you.

334
00:19:02,609 --> 00:19:06,813
In Africa, one out of five children
is starving.

335
00:19:07,413 --> 00:19:12,151
Even in Japan, one in seven children
lives in poverty.

336
00:19:12,452 --> 00:19:16,556
If you have the nerve to say
that you are not fond of sweets,

337
00:19:16,923 --> 00:19:19,626
then take this to a pitiful child.

338
00:19:20,093 --> 00:19:21,995
-You are absolutely right.
-Yes.

339
00:19:22,795 --> 00:19:27,166
Last night, I missed the last train
and stayed at an internet cafe.

340
00:19:27,934 --> 00:19:30,169
Those people are pitiful as well.

341
00:19:31,271 --> 00:19:32,572
-Eat!
-Yes!

342
00:19:34,941 --> 00:19:37,076
-By the way…
-Yes?

343
00:19:37,143 --> 00:19:40,513
Why did that woman come?

344
00:19:41,114 --> 00:19:43,216
That woman? Do you mean Sangenya?

345
00:19:44,150 --> 00:19:46,753
Maybe she likes you.

346
00:19:46,819 --> 00:19:50,623
No, I don't think so. Sangenya is married.

347
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:55,328
Whether you are married or not is
not an issue for a man and a woman.

348
00:19:55,395 --> 00:19:57,830
When things happen, they just happen!

349
00:19:58,164 --> 00:20:00,366
Is that so?

350
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:02,535
After all, you are her cute subordinate,

351
00:20:02,602 --> 00:20:06,239
and you aren't very dependable.

352
00:20:06,973 --> 00:20:09,642
Well, I'm sure she doesn't dislike me,
but I'm not sure

353
00:20:09,709 --> 00:20:10,743
if she likes me.

354
00:20:11,411 --> 00:20:13,246
-Let's go out to drink!
-What?

355
00:20:23,957 --> 00:20:25,625
Welcome!

356
00:20:25,692 --> 00:20:26,726
Oh, Mr. Rusudo.

357
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:28,061
Good evening.

358
00:20:28,127 --> 00:20:33,266
It's amazing how handsome guys
have gathered around an ugly hostess.

359
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,767
Oh? Where's Kokoro?

360
00:20:35,101 --> 00:20:37,737
Today, I'm here by myself
until the morning.

361
00:20:37,804 --> 00:20:38,771
We lost out today.

362
00:20:39,205 --> 00:20:42,842
And why is your nose bleeding again, Mika?

363
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:46,779
When the two of them are here,
I can't help but have a nose bleed.

364
00:20:46,846 --> 00:20:48,281
That's because she's in heat.

365
00:20:52,018 --> 00:20:53,086
How wonderful.

366
00:20:53,152 --> 00:20:55,054
You sure are good looking.

367
00:20:56,189 --> 00:20:57,390
I'm Rusudo.

368
00:20:58,191 --> 00:20:59,826
Oh, you are a realtor too?

369
00:21:00,059 --> 00:21:01,260
Call me anytime.

370
00:21:01,928 --> 00:21:04,130
Mr. Rusudo, Ms. Kamiko is my client.

371
00:21:04,197 --> 00:21:06,366
I know, Niwano.

372
00:21:06,432 --> 00:21:09,402
Hey, get two bottles of champagne
for the good-looking guys.

373
00:21:09,469 --> 00:21:12,405
I'm sorry. We don't have such
a fancy drink here.

374
00:21:12,472 --> 00:21:15,508
What? Then go buy one! Here you go.

375
00:21:15,575 --> 00:21:18,077
My name is Shirasu.

376
00:21:18,144 --> 00:21:20,613
Who cares, Bloody Nose. Go buy it now!

377
00:21:21,748 --> 00:21:22,749
INSTANT NOODLES

378
00:21:22,982 --> 00:21:24,784
Hungarian cuisine is a bit…

379
00:21:25,318 --> 00:21:26,319
Manager.

380
00:21:28,554 --> 00:21:30,323
You want to eat ramen?

381
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:33,593
Sangenya, what are you doing here?

382
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:36,229
I had a little time, so I'm shopping.

383
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:39,866
Oh, then we can eat dinner
together tonight?

384
00:21:40,099 --> 00:21:42,769
I can't eat dinner with you.
I'll be going back to work.

385
00:21:42,835 --> 00:21:44,370
If you would like to eat ramen--

386
00:21:44,604 --> 00:21:50,777
No, no, I'll be eating
the Hungarian dish you prepared.

387
00:21:51,177 --> 00:21:53,413
Well, I have some more shopping to do.

388
00:21:53,479 --> 00:21:54,981
Can I come along?

389
00:21:55,782 --> 00:21:56,783
Of course.

390
00:21:59,519 --> 00:22:02,121
It doesn't have to be such expensive meat.

391
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:05,324
I thought you liked beef.

392
00:22:05,725 --> 00:22:09,629
I do, but that's expensive.
This costs ¥2,000 per 100 grams.

393
00:22:10,163 --> 00:22:11,330
I have money.

394
00:22:11,831 --> 00:22:13,099
Really?

395
00:22:13,433 --> 00:22:15,668
What do you mean by "really"?

396
00:22:16,135 --> 00:22:18,237
Sanchi Real Estate was quite profitable.

397
00:22:18,304 --> 00:22:23,643
But we promised to save up that money
for when we get older,

398
00:22:23,710 --> 00:22:26,646
so let's not buy beef
that's ¥2,000 per 100 grams.

399
00:22:27,613 --> 00:22:28,881
Then I'll choose chicken.

400
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,823
What are you upset about?
People are watching.

401
00:22:38,758 --> 00:22:40,560
I haven't done anything
that's embarrassing.

402
00:22:40,927 --> 00:22:42,462
We were only discussing

403
00:22:42,528 --> 00:22:45,298
how to manage our household,
and how to buy meat.

404
00:22:46,199 --> 00:22:48,434
I think it's important
for a husband and wife

405
00:22:48,768 --> 00:22:53,606
to discuss these matters properly.
Isn't that the case for you?

406
00:22:53,940 --> 00:22:54,941
You are right.

407
00:22:55,341 --> 00:22:56,976
I'll pick cheap chicken wings.

408
00:22:58,010 --> 00:22:59,212
Are you satisfied?

409
00:22:59,278 --> 00:23:01,547
The way you say it is a bit…

410
00:23:01,781 --> 00:23:03,516
This is how I always speak.

411
00:23:03,783 --> 00:23:06,719
Since we're having a "discussion",
I'd like to say something.

412
00:23:06,786 --> 00:23:09,689
We don't have to eat
restaurant-quality cuisine at home.

413
00:23:10,056 --> 00:23:10,890
What?

414
00:23:10,957 --> 00:23:13,459
Well, when we're eating at home,

415
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,962
breakfast can be white rice
with miso soup,

416
00:23:16,028 --> 00:23:18,931
and maybe natto or pickled plum.
That's enough.

417
00:23:19,232 --> 00:23:22,468
For dinner, rather than a steak,
simmered flounder and pickled vegetables,

418
00:23:22,535 --> 00:23:26,005
is more than good enough for me.
What do you think?

419
00:23:26,606 --> 00:23:29,075
Does that mean you don't like my cooking?

420
00:23:29,142 --> 00:23:32,478
That's not it.
This is a discussion, right?

421
00:23:32,545 --> 00:23:36,282
Your cooking skills are amazing,
and I am grateful for it, but--

422
00:23:36,349 --> 00:23:37,416
But?

423
00:23:38,951 --> 00:23:44,357
I don't feel at home when breakfast
is like that of a first-class hotel.

424
00:23:44,757 --> 00:23:46,559
I get exhausted even before going to work.

425
00:23:47,126 --> 00:23:48,327
I see.

426
00:23:48,394 --> 00:23:51,230
So you have been eating my breakfast

427
00:23:51,297 --> 00:23:53,800
feeling that way all this time?

428
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:55,735
I am grateful though.

429
00:23:56,269 --> 00:23:57,837
You are grateful, but you didn't like it.

430
00:23:57,904 --> 00:24:01,541
I didn't say I dislike it.
I'm just saying I get a bit tired.

431
00:24:01,607 --> 00:24:03,709
Something less sophisticated…

432
00:24:03,776 --> 00:24:06,112
like Chichin Pui Pui's soggy
fried noodles?

433
00:24:06,179 --> 00:24:10,349
I just want you to know that
food like that is more comforting for me.

434
00:24:10,783 --> 00:24:13,352
Chichin Pui Pui's soggy fried noodles?

435
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:15,221
I'll go learn it.

436
00:24:15,288 --> 00:24:17,356
No, no! That's not what I meant.

437
00:24:17,623 --> 00:24:19,892
I'm sorry that I'm such
an incompetent wife.

438
00:24:19,959 --> 00:24:23,129
I will make changes, so please forgive me.

439
00:24:23,196 --> 00:24:26,799
Well, it's not about forgiving
or not forgiving…

440
00:24:26,866 --> 00:24:29,101
What I'm trying to say is not
really getting through to you.

441
00:24:29,168 --> 00:24:34,173
No, I totally get it. I've lost time
so I'll go back to shopping.

442
00:24:39,045 --> 00:24:41,480
Now, I'm going back to work.

443
00:24:41,781 --> 00:24:42,915
Good luck.

444
00:24:42,982 --> 00:24:45,785
I will be the one to sell a house
to Ms. Kamiko.

445
00:24:46,085 --> 00:24:48,354
It won't be Niwano.
I will sell her a house.

446
00:24:48,921 --> 00:24:50,223
What's the prospect?

447
00:24:50,489 --> 00:24:53,025
There is no house I can't sell!

448
00:24:53,092 --> 00:24:54,994
SALE

449
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,768
Thank you. I'm leaving now.

450
00:25:03,202 --> 00:25:06,305
-Then I'm going too.
-Mr. Adachi, stay a little longer!

451
00:25:06,372 --> 00:25:07,607
You stay.

452
00:25:09,909 --> 00:25:10,910
Mr. Rusudo.

453
00:25:12,044 --> 00:25:13,045
You pull it.

454
00:25:15,581 --> 00:25:16,582
Thank you.

455
00:25:17,183 --> 00:25:22,221
One good-looking guy left since
there's no champagne here! Go buy more.

456
00:25:22,288 --> 00:25:23,823
We are about to close.

457
00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:26,726
Oh, Ms. Kamiko, I'll take
you home in a taxi then.

458
00:25:26,792 --> 00:25:29,528
-My home?
-You live in the Setagaya area, right?

459
00:25:29,595 --> 00:25:31,597
-No, I can go home by myself.
-I'll help you.

460
00:25:31,664 --> 00:25:34,233
-You are annoying! You are too persistent!
-Sorry.

461
00:25:35,301 --> 00:25:36,369
See you!

462
00:25:41,607 --> 00:25:45,044
What happened?
Why was she upset all of a sudden?

463
00:25:55,154 --> 00:25:57,189
I won't make it in time…

464
00:25:57,723 --> 00:25:58,591
RECEPTION

465
00:25:58,658 --> 00:25:59,725
Welcome.

466
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:05,031
Could I get the overnight package,
single-size room?

467
00:26:05,364 --> 00:26:06,799
Cancel that!

468
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:08,734
Chief Sangenya?

469
00:26:08,968 --> 00:26:11,037
Overnight package, couple's seat please.

470
00:26:11,404 --> 00:26:13,372
Why are you here?

471
00:26:13,439 --> 00:26:15,508
Why is it a couple's seat? What?

472
00:26:15,574 --> 00:26:18,244
Why are we getting the couple's seat?

473
00:26:18,544 --> 00:26:19,378
It's reasonably priced.

474
00:26:19,445 --> 00:26:23,749
Reasonable? Even if it's reasonable,
you are married.

475
00:26:24,083 --> 00:26:26,686
It's room 402. Go right now. Go!

476
00:26:26,752 --> 00:26:27,753
Yes!

477
00:26:31,324 --> 00:26:34,794
-Everything is to sell a house!
-What?

478
00:26:34,860 --> 00:26:35,861
24 HOURS ALL YEAR LONG!

479
00:26:42,702 --> 00:26:46,339
Um… Are you going to read
a comic or something?

480
00:26:47,006 --> 00:26:49,342
I won't read. We are working right now.

481
00:26:50,910 --> 00:26:52,712
Right.

482
00:26:53,479 --> 00:26:56,282
Chief Sangenya and I
are working right now.

483
00:26:59,151 --> 00:27:01,420
You are here to sell a house, right?

484
00:27:01,721 --> 00:27:04,724
Yes, it's to sell a house.

485
00:27:06,692 --> 00:27:08,928
Well… Well…

486
00:27:09,362 --> 00:27:10,363
What?

487
00:27:10,429 --> 00:27:14,600
Um no, does Manager know about this?

488
00:27:15,301 --> 00:27:16,736
What do you mean by "about this"?

489
00:27:18,537 --> 00:27:22,842
We're here to sell a house,
and nothing more than that,

490
00:27:23,576 --> 00:27:27,880
but does Manager know that you and I
are in this small space together?

491
00:27:27,947 --> 00:27:30,649
If we sell a house, Manager
won't complain about it.

492
00:27:34,587 --> 00:27:36,322
-Niwano.
-Yes?

493
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:39,558
-Go take a shower.
-What?

494
00:27:40,126 --> 00:27:41,927
-Your nose is bleeding.
-What?

495
00:27:54,473 --> 00:27:55,975
Ms. Kamiko?

496
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:58,010
Ah! That towel!

497
00:28:07,787 --> 00:28:12,024
Oh, this song!
So that's what this is all about!

498
00:28:13,125 --> 00:28:14,160
Hello?

499
00:28:15,027 --> 00:28:18,664
Ms. Kamiko, do you stay at a place
like this once in a while?

500
00:28:19,732 --> 00:28:21,667
I thought you went home in a taxi.

501
00:28:23,602 --> 00:28:27,873
I'm surprised to find out that you've been
living at an internet cafe.

502
00:28:29,108 --> 00:28:31,343
You have a lot saved up,
so why are you here?

503
00:28:33,012 --> 00:28:35,181
You said at a cafe this afternoon

504
00:28:36,282 --> 00:28:38,384
that one in five people
is starving in Africa,

505
00:28:39,118 --> 00:28:42,254
and even in Japan, one in seven
children lives in poverty.

506
00:28:43,255 --> 00:28:44,523
Like I said earlier today,

507
00:28:45,024 --> 00:28:46,725
the people here are pitiful.

508
00:28:47,993 --> 00:28:50,229
Let's go home. I will take you home.

509
00:28:51,797 --> 00:28:52,798
Ms. Kamiko.

510
00:28:55,201 --> 00:28:56,268
Ms. Kamiko.

511
00:29:00,139 --> 00:29:01,140
Mr. Rusudo?

512
00:29:04,977 --> 00:29:05,978
Niwano.

513
00:29:06,946 --> 00:29:10,049
I think your understanding is a bit off.

514
00:29:11,450 --> 00:29:12,485
Rusudo.

515
00:29:12,885 --> 00:29:14,420
Why are you here?

516
00:29:15,020 --> 00:29:16,789
There's nothing pitiful about being here.

517
00:29:17,857 --> 00:29:20,059
That's why everyone is here.

518
00:29:22,528 --> 00:29:25,698
By the way, I'm also
a regular customer here.

519
00:29:26,632 --> 00:29:28,434
Currently, I've been here for 30 nights.

520
00:29:31,003 --> 00:29:33,906
Let's go talk in my room.

521
00:29:34,340 --> 00:29:35,341
What?

522
00:29:38,410 --> 00:29:39,778
-Sit down.
-Yes.

523
00:29:42,448 --> 00:29:45,151
Ah, I can tell that you've been
here for 30 nights.

524
00:29:50,256 --> 00:29:56,228
You said it's not pitiful at all,
but what do you mean by that?

525
00:29:57,096 --> 00:30:00,232
For example, the lady in room 203

526
00:30:00,900 --> 00:30:02,468
came to Tokyo from the countryside.

527
00:30:02,735 --> 00:30:06,639
She spends three nights a week
at her boyfriend's place,

528
00:30:06,972 --> 00:30:09,175
but she stays here the rest of the time.

529
00:30:10,042 --> 00:30:15,047
Her current boyfriend
is dating multiple women,

530
00:30:15,481 --> 00:30:20,986
but she believes that he will
sort out his other relationships

531
00:30:21,487 --> 00:30:26,025
to live with her like he promised.
So she's here in the meantime.

532
00:30:27,193 --> 00:30:30,996
Living at an internet cafe instead
of renting a room in Tokyo

533
00:30:31,797 --> 00:30:34,333
means that she's betting on her
future with him.

534
00:30:35,201 --> 00:30:39,805
This is a place of hope for her.

535
00:30:41,040 --> 00:30:43,876
Is it like making a wish?

536
00:30:45,511 --> 00:30:49,014
If her wish doesn't come true,
then she'll leave this place.

537
00:30:51,083 --> 00:30:54,186
Next, the man in room 306,

538
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,989
works as a construction worker

539
00:30:57,656 --> 00:30:59,758
and makes ¥300,000 per month.

540
00:30:59,825 --> 00:31:01,760
Then he doesn't have to live here.

541
00:31:02,294 --> 00:31:04,163
Construction sites change every day.

542
00:31:05,064 --> 00:31:08,434
It's more productive and is better
for his sleep

543
00:31:09,335 --> 00:31:11,937
to stay at a place that's closest
to his work site the next day.

544
00:31:13,472 --> 00:31:16,742
There are people who see no value

545
00:31:17,243 --> 00:31:19,378
in having their own place.

546
00:31:20,279 --> 00:31:21,647
Is that possible?

547
00:31:22,314 --> 00:31:26,318
Niwano, you don't think
someone is a mature adult unless

548
00:31:27,052 --> 00:31:28,854
they own a home, huh?

549
00:31:31,357 --> 00:31:34,860
In this day and age,
our values have diversified.

550
00:31:35,461 --> 00:31:37,129
And there are different lifestyles.

551
00:31:38,130 --> 00:31:40,266
This place has a roof,

552
00:31:40,332 --> 00:31:45,371
a shower, a computer,
and a cafe space. This internet cafe

553
00:31:46,005 --> 00:31:49,441
could be considered
as one's portable home.

554
00:31:50,542 --> 00:31:53,512
People who live here

555
00:31:54,847 --> 00:31:57,716
shouldn't be pitied.

556
00:32:00,853 --> 00:32:01,854
Come in.

557
00:32:05,057 --> 00:32:06,659
You say great things.

558
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:09,495
Please, come in.

559
00:32:13,866 --> 00:32:17,136
Ms. Kamiko, you like it here too?

560
00:32:18,304 --> 00:32:20,506
Well, it's not quite like that.

561
00:32:22,141 --> 00:32:25,844
I was living in a rundown
apartment building all my life.

562
00:32:27,579 --> 00:32:29,782
I do have quite a bit of money.

563
00:32:30,749 --> 00:32:33,619
But I was told the apartment
is going to be demolished.

564
00:32:34,453 --> 00:32:38,424
So I searched for another apartment,

565
00:32:39,024 --> 00:32:41,560
but no one would rent to me.

566
00:32:45,364 --> 00:32:47,633
They are afraid that I'll die alone
and unattended.

567
00:32:49,268 --> 00:32:51,570
All the apartments I looked at
told me that.

568
00:32:54,073 --> 00:32:55,741
Before I could find a new place,

569
00:32:58,243 --> 00:33:00,079
my apartment was demolished

570
00:33:03,682 --> 00:33:05,651
and I've been living here
for several months.

571
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:09,755
This place is not so bad.

572
00:33:10,956 --> 00:33:13,092
There's always someone here.

573
00:33:14,593 --> 00:33:17,629
The employees here are nice to me too.

574
00:33:19,765 --> 00:33:22,735
But you came to Teiko Real Estate

575
00:33:23,168 --> 00:33:26,739
thinking of buying a place,
because you couldn't rent, right?

576
00:33:28,674 --> 00:33:30,109
Even if I buy a house,

577
00:33:32,978 --> 00:33:34,646
if I live alone,

578
00:33:36,415 --> 00:33:39,151
I realized that I'd die all alone anyway.

579
00:33:40,686 --> 00:33:44,323
But, you were working so hard,

580
00:33:44,890 --> 00:33:46,992
so I couldn't back down anymore.

581
00:33:47,826 --> 00:33:48,861
I'm sorry

582
00:33:50,329 --> 00:33:51,797
for dragging you around everywhere.

583
00:33:54,233 --> 00:33:59,204
I don't want to die alone!

584
00:34:04,243 --> 00:34:06,779
I don't want to die alone…

585
00:34:08,213 --> 00:34:09,948
I don't want to die alone…

586
00:34:11,784 --> 00:34:13,619
That is lonely indeed.

587
00:34:17,990 --> 00:34:20,826
I'm all alone too.

588
00:34:22,661 --> 00:34:23,796
Is that true?

589
00:34:25,264 --> 00:34:30,903
I understand how lonely
you feel, Ms. Kamiko.

590
00:34:46,218 --> 00:34:48,153
My nose stopped bleeding,

591
00:34:49,421 --> 00:34:52,458
but I don't understand anything anymore.

592
00:34:53,592 --> 00:34:55,527
-Niwano.
-Yes?

593
00:34:56,261 --> 00:34:58,497
You can't sell a house
with just your kindness.

594
00:35:00,632 --> 00:35:02,434
HINODE BANK

595
00:35:11,610 --> 00:35:13,412
WELCOME, PLEASE CHOOSE YOUR
DESIRED TRANSACTION

596
00:35:14,046 --> 00:35:17,716
Should I withdraw ¥10,000? Or ¥15,000?
No, maybe ¥10,000?

597
00:35:17,783 --> 00:35:18,784
Well, I guess ¥10,000.

598
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:22,621
ZERO BALANCE. IT CAN'T BE WITHDRAWN

599
00:35:22,688 --> 00:35:25,491
Zero? Zero balance?

600
00:35:26,325 --> 00:35:27,960
There are houses that have

601
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:30,529
sensors everywhere,
and a security company will be called

602
00:35:30,596 --> 00:35:31,964
if no movement is detected.

603
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:37,669
But I think for Ms. Kamiko, a facility
with great nursing care is best.

604
00:35:37,903 --> 00:35:39,838
But then you won't be able
to sell a house.

605
00:35:39,905 --> 00:35:43,008
That's… right.

606
00:35:45,410 --> 00:35:47,713
Niwano, you are kind.

607
00:35:48,647 --> 00:35:54,486
I think it's impossible to make
her happy by selling her a house.

608
00:35:54,853 --> 00:35:56,321
Right.

609
00:35:58,924 --> 00:36:02,127
I made up my mind. Thank you very much.

610
00:36:03,428 --> 00:36:05,731
I haven't done anything
you should thank me for.

611
00:36:08,100 --> 00:36:10,936
-Um, could I ask you one thing?
-What?

612
00:36:11,570 --> 00:36:15,674
Why have you stayed at the internet
cafe for 30 days?

613
00:36:17,309 --> 00:36:18,710
That's because…

614
00:36:21,513 --> 00:36:22,814
It's full of treasures.

615
00:36:23,615 --> 00:36:25,317
Full of treasures?

616
00:36:26,585 --> 00:36:27,986
OASIS HIDAMARI

617
00:36:28,053 --> 00:36:32,324
They all have private rooms
and ample nursing staff.

618
00:36:33,091 --> 00:36:36,862
This won't profit you a cent, right?

619
00:36:37,162 --> 00:36:40,799
Right, but I want to be of help
since our paths have crossed.

620
00:36:41,333 --> 00:36:44,703
That slender guy and you are both so nice.

621
00:36:44,770 --> 00:36:46,405
Being nice won't sell a house,

622
00:36:47,039 --> 00:36:48,707
is what my superior tells me every day.

623
00:36:48,774 --> 00:36:50,509
-That beautiful superior of yours?
-Yes.

624
00:36:50,842 --> 00:36:51,843
Oh my!

625
00:36:51,910 --> 00:36:56,815
How nice. You are here to see this
place with your grandson? How lovely!

626
00:36:56,882 --> 00:37:00,919
I'm not a baby. I'm an elderly!

627
00:37:02,087 --> 00:37:03,088
What's the matter?

628
00:37:03,589 --> 00:37:05,791
Don't ridicule the elderly! Talk normally!

629
00:37:05,857 --> 00:37:07,593
You can talk like a regular person, right?

630
00:37:08,193 --> 00:37:10,329
No! I won't take this anymore!

631
00:37:10,629 --> 00:37:13,765
I can't live in a place like this
full of all these old people!

632
00:37:14,066 --> 00:37:18,270
I don't need to be taken care of.
I can live and take care of myself!

633
00:37:18,537 --> 00:37:22,441
How dare you speak to me like that?
Who do you think you are?

634
00:37:22,507 --> 00:37:24,977
What's wrong with you, Niwano!

635
00:37:25,043 --> 00:37:27,245
I don't want to be stuck with these
old people!

636
00:37:27,312 --> 00:37:31,083
I want to live with
all sorts of people! I'm leaving.

637
00:37:32,217 --> 00:37:34,953
-Where are you going?
-I can only go to that internet cafe!

638
00:37:35,754 --> 00:37:37,055
Please wait!

639
00:37:37,122 --> 00:37:37,990
COELACANTH

640
00:37:38,056 --> 00:37:40,292
-Welcome.
-My usual.

641
00:37:42,361 --> 00:37:43,562
WE WILL CLOSE IN THREE DAYS.

642
00:37:43,629 --> 00:37:45,030
PLEASE LEAVE WITHIN THREE DAYS

643
00:37:45,097 --> 00:37:46,098
What is this?

644
00:37:46,832 --> 00:37:47,899
You are going to close?

645
00:37:48,133 --> 00:37:50,435
Looks like it. I don't know,
since I only work here part-time.

646
00:37:50,502 --> 00:37:52,404
What should I do once this place is gone?

647
00:37:53,105 --> 00:37:54,673
There are other internet cafes as well.

648
00:37:54,740 --> 00:37:59,544
No, I like it here. I don't want
to go to a new place now.

649
00:37:59,611 --> 00:38:00,612
There's nothing I can do.

650
00:38:00,879 --> 00:38:03,248
Could you tell the owner about it?

651
00:38:04,349 --> 00:38:05,517
I'm the owner.

652
00:38:05,851 --> 00:38:07,986
-What?
-Chief Sangenya, why are you here?

653
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:09,287
Are you serious?

654
00:38:09,554 --> 00:38:12,824
I bought this whole place just now.
I paid for it out of pocket.

655
00:38:13,191 --> 00:38:15,093
-Just now?
-What the heck?

656
00:38:15,527 --> 00:38:16,962
To close this place.

657
00:38:18,163 --> 00:38:21,767
This sort of place
should be shut down and destroyed!

658
00:38:25,070 --> 00:38:27,072
This place is where drifters
of society hang out.

659
00:38:27,472 --> 00:38:29,841
Only trash lives here.

660
00:38:30,108 --> 00:38:31,710
A lady in 203

661
00:38:31,943 --> 00:38:34,913
doesn't want to acknowledge
that she's not loved by her man.

662
00:38:34,980 --> 00:38:37,916
Even if you wait 100 years,
that man won't be yours.

663
00:38:39,251 --> 00:38:41,586
-She'll hear you.
-I don't care if she hears me!

664
00:38:42,354 --> 00:38:44,089
You, in room 203.

665
00:38:44,156 --> 00:38:48,260
You are escaping reality using
a man's actions as an excuse.

666
00:38:48,527 --> 00:38:52,064
The guy with the temporary job
in room 306.

667
00:38:52,130 --> 00:38:56,068
It is not rare that the location
of work changes every day.

668
00:38:56,368 --> 00:39:00,305
It isn't rare for a work location
and your home to be far apart

669
00:39:00,372 --> 00:39:02,874
due to transfers and other changes.
It's what all business men face.

670
00:39:02,941 --> 00:39:05,844
You are running away from your future

671
00:39:05,911 --> 00:39:08,280
that you must face when you rent
or purchase a home.

672
00:39:09,047 --> 00:39:10,916
And you…

673
00:39:11,750 --> 00:39:14,352
live here saying that you are scared
of dying alone.

674
00:39:15,153 --> 00:39:18,757
However, all humans die alone.

675
00:39:19,524 --> 00:39:23,128
Whether you die unattended,
or die surrounded by your family,

676
00:39:23,195 --> 00:39:24,896
you still die alone.

677
00:39:25,230 --> 00:39:30,035
If you don't know that at your age,
you are just a spoiled brat.

678
00:39:30,368 --> 00:39:32,070
Please stop, Chief Sangenya.

679
00:39:32,404 --> 00:39:36,942
All these people here are spoiled brats
who've given up trying.

680
00:39:37,242 --> 00:39:39,911
Spoiled brats
who can't stand strong today,

681
00:39:39,978 --> 00:39:42,214
will never get to see tomorrow's sunrise.

682
00:39:42,681 --> 00:39:45,550
There is no future for someone
who makes excuses,

683
00:39:45,617 --> 00:39:47,786
saying that they'll start
doing their best tomorrow.

684
00:39:50,355 --> 00:39:51,356
You're wrong.

685
00:39:52,824 --> 00:39:54,893
Tomorrow still comes to those who couldn't

686
00:39:55,660 --> 00:39:56,895
do their best today.

687
00:39:57,896 --> 00:40:01,733
Life continues. That's why people suffer.

688
00:40:03,068 --> 00:40:06,138
Someone like you
who's beautiful and talented,

689
00:40:06,671 --> 00:40:08,940
who works for a great company
and makes plenty of money,

690
00:40:09,708 --> 00:40:14,179
who got married to the manager
and is leading a confident life,

691
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:19,618
wouldn't understand that
everyone else is disadvantaged.

692
00:40:20,152 --> 00:40:23,655
No matter how hard you try,
there are some who just can't do it.

693
00:40:25,757 --> 00:40:28,860
Everyone here is living a life like that.

694
00:40:29,728 --> 00:40:32,397
Even hangouts for drifters
are necessary for society!

695
00:40:33,198 --> 00:40:38,136
If there are no hangouts for drifters,
where would we go?

696
00:40:38,203 --> 00:40:39,204
Then

697
00:40:41,173 --> 00:40:43,708
why don't you buy this place from me

698
00:40:44,142 --> 00:40:46,878
and build a palace for drifters?

699
00:40:49,714 --> 00:40:53,585
You will be the owner
and resident of this internet cafe.

700
00:40:55,287 --> 00:40:57,589
That's not possible.

701
00:41:00,325 --> 00:41:02,828
Ms. Kamiko, you are able to do it.

702
00:41:03,995 --> 00:41:07,165
You have the money to purchase this place.

703
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:08,700
You are the only one

704
00:41:08,767 --> 00:41:12,304
who can make this place into a home
that would be a palace for drifters.

705
00:41:27,752 --> 00:41:29,688
This is not good. Let's run away.

706
00:41:36,328 --> 00:41:39,598
-Please buy it.
-You are the only one.

707
00:41:39,664 --> 00:41:41,132
-Please!
-We're begging you.

708
00:41:41,666 --> 00:41:44,603
-Please!
-Please buy it.

709
00:41:56,948 --> 00:41:58,016
I've got her.

710
00:42:05,891 --> 00:42:06,892
I'm going to the restroom.

711
00:42:08,460 --> 00:42:09,461
She's copying me.

712
00:42:12,030 --> 00:42:13,031
Welcome back.

713
00:42:13,932 --> 00:42:16,167
-Where's Sangenya?
-She's not back yet.

714
00:42:16,234 --> 00:42:17,502
You okay? You don't look well.

715
00:42:18,203 --> 00:42:19,204
Mr. Fuse…

716
00:42:20,739 --> 00:42:24,009
My family savings is all gone.

717
00:42:24,276 --> 00:42:26,411
-What?
-The balance is zero!

718
00:42:27,412 --> 00:42:28,546
Did someone take it?

719
00:42:28,613 --> 00:42:31,349
I don't want to think like that,
I don't want to think like that,

720
00:42:31,416 --> 00:42:33,385
but someone who can withdraw
money besides me is…

721
00:42:34,219 --> 00:42:36,421
only Sangenya.

722
00:42:36,955 --> 00:42:39,524
She withdrew money
and ran off with another guy?

723
00:42:41,459 --> 00:42:44,796
-I don't want to think that!
-That's the only possibility!

724
00:42:44,863 --> 00:42:45,897
Manager.

725
00:42:47,399 --> 00:42:48,433
Sangenya!

726
00:42:48,867 --> 00:42:52,203
I don't have another man. I am your wife.

727
00:42:52,704 --> 00:42:57,309
Pardon me. Manager Yashiro
was so disturbed that it slipped.

728
00:42:57,375 --> 00:42:58,476
-Manager.
-Yes.

729
00:42:58,977 --> 00:43:02,347
The money I withdrew is returned
plus an additional six million yen.

730
00:43:03,348 --> 00:43:05,650
-What?
-Six million?

731
00:43:05,717 --> 00:43:06,718
Don't look.

732
00:43:09,020 --> 00:43:13,458
It was just zero, but now it's back
plus six million. What's going on?

733
00:43:13,525 --> 00:43:15,961
We profited six million.

734
00:43:16,027 --> 00:43:17,028
What?

735
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:29,941
Internet cafe.

736
00:43:30,809 --> 00:43:31,643
Old hag?

737
00:43:31,710 --> 00:43:32,811
INTERNET CAFE, OLD HAG

738
00:43:40,185 --> 00:43:41,453
OLD HAG'S GREEN TEA

739
00:43:41,519 --> 00:43:43,188
OLD HAG'S PHONE SERVICE
WAKE UP SERVICE IS AVAILABLE NOW

740
00:43:43,254 --> 00:43:44,356
Not yet?

741
00:43:44,756 --> 00:43:48,326
Don't rush me.
I'm making you delicious tea!

742
00:43:48,393 --> 00:43:51,730
Sorry! It took so long.
I was worried you collapsed back there.

743
00:43:51,796 --> 00:43:54,833
Don't worry about me.
I'll live longer than you.

744
00:43:55,433 --> 00:43:56,668
Thank you for the tea.

745
00:43:56,735 --> 00:43:58,303
-Hello.
-Oh!

746
00:43:58,370 --> 00:43:59,437
Niwano, what's going on?

747
00:43:59,738 --> 00:44:01,773
I was close by, so I came
to see you, Ms. Kamiko.

748
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:04,009
Don't say something you don't mean.

749
00:44:04,075 --> 00:44:07,579
Don't talk like that. If I miss
my last train, I might stay here.

750
00:44:07,645 --> 00:44:10,982
Oh, I'm sorry, but this place
has been really full lately.

751
00:44:11,049 --> 00:44:12,517
So make a reservation, okay?

752
00:44:12,584 --> 00:44:14,119
It's that busy?

753
00:44:14,552 --> 00:44:16,354
It's a palace for drifters!

754
00:44:18,957 --> 00:44:20,025
Chief Sangenya?

755
00:44:20,091 --> 00:44:21,726
You were goofing off here?

756
00:44:21,793 --> 00:44:23,194
Um no, I was just…

757
00:44:23,261 --> 00:44:27,565
Tominaga! Uchimura! Sangenya is here!

758
00:44:27,632 --> 00:44:28,633
Coming!

759
00:44:37,575 --> 00:44:39,978
I will now be selling properties here.

760
00:44:40,512 --> 00:44:41,546
What?

761
00:44:41,613 --> 00:44:43,515
APPLICATION TO PURCHASE A PROPERTY

762
00:44:44,349 --> 00:44:47,385
That girl who got dumped
and that temp job guy

763
00:44:48,119 --> 00:44:50,121
saw eye to eye
and now they're getting married.

764
00:44:50,355 --> 00:44:52,824
And they're buying
a house from that woman.

765
00:44:53,758 --> 00:44:54,859
What?

766
00:44:54,926 --> 00:44:58,029
That woman went around
many different internet cafes

767
00:44:58,430 --> 00:45:00,732
looking for potential clients.

768
00:45:01,466 --> 00:45:02,300
What?

769
00:45:02,567 --> 00:45:06,371
She knew that I was here at this
internet cafe from that time

770
00:45:06,638 --> 00:45:08,640
in front of the elevator
at Teiko Real Estate.

771
00:45:09,340 --> 00:45:11,009
She found out from my humming.

772
00:45:11,476 --> 00:45:15,146
Ancient fish, ancient fish,
a living fossil.

773
00:45:19,484 --> 00:45:22,353
Everything went
just as that woman planned.

774
00:45:24,722 --> 00:45:26,558
Thankfully, I sold a house.

775
00:45:26,624 --> 00:45:28,927
I will be counting on your
information again.

776
00:45:29,561 --> 00:45:30,562
Of course!

777
00:45:33,498 --> 00:45:35,867
Chief Sangenya,

778
00:45:35,934 --> 00:45:38,736
were you planning to sell houses
to those people from the beginning?

779
00:45:38,803 --> 00:45:39,904
Yes!

780
00:45:39,971 --> 00:45:42,307
So you were going around
internet cafes to sell houses?

781
00:45:42,373 --> 00:45:45,176
-Right.
-But why can you sell houses there?

782
00:45:45,977 --> 00:45:47,879
That's why you can't sell a house, Niwano!

783
00:45:48,379 --> 00:45:49,214
What?

784
00:45:49,447 --> 00:45:52,250
Internet cafes are full of people
without homes.

785
00:45:52,650 --> 00:45:55,954
In other words, for a realtor,
it's full of treasures!

786
00:45:57,088 --> 00:45:58,089
I see…

787
00:46:01,593 --> 00:46:04,195
Why have you stayed
at the internet cafe for 30 days?

788
00:46:06,231 --> 00:46:07,565
It's full of treasures.

789
00:46:08,433 --> 00:46:12,303
Was Rusudo also planning
to sell to the internet cafe residents?

790
00:46:12,570 --> 00:46:16,508
That's right. One-third of them
were taken by Rusudo.

791
00:46:21,312 --> 00:46:23,248
So that's what happened.

792
00:46:23,815 --> 00:46:25,917
Chief Sangenya is hard to understand,

793
00:46:26,184 --> 00:46:29,888
but Mr. Rusudo is hard
to understand as well.

794
00:46:29,954 --> 00:46:30,955
I really don't get them.

795
00:46:31,189 --> 00:46:33,258
We need to watch out for that Rusudo guy.

796
00:46:34,592 --> 00:46:38,763
That's not true!
A good-looking guy is never evil!

797
00:46:40,098 --> 00:46:42,700
-Mr. Rusudo, these two were just--
-Hey, hey!

798
00:46:43,101 --> 00:46:44,602
Is Chief Sangenya late tonight too?

799
00:46:45,436 --> 00:46:48,706
Well, usually she's late every night.

800
00:46:49,307 --> 00:46:50,475
When it's like that,

801
00:46:50,542 --> 00:46:52,744
do you go to bed beforehand, Yashiro?

802
00:46:53,211 --> 00:46:55,013
Well, yes.

803
00:46:55,847 --> 00:46:59,317
Even when she's late every night,
breakfast is a full-course meal.

804
00:47:01,119 --> 00:47:02,187
Recently,

805
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:05,690
she found me trying to buy
instant ramen noodles at a store.

806
00:47:05,757 --> 00:47:07,458
The following day, breakfast was…

807
00:47:08,893 --> 00:47:11,829
Shark fin ramen noodles.

808
00:47:12,163 --> 00:47:15,166
Shark fin ramen noodles!
Could I take a look?

809
00:47:15,233 --> 00:47:17,268
Well, if you insist.

810
00:47:19,404 --> 00:47:21,739
-This is it.
-Wow, how extravagant!

811
00:47:22,540 --> 00:47:27,111
It's creepy that your breakfast
was shark-fin ramen noodles!

812
00:47:27,178 --> 00:47:29,614
By the way, where's Kokoro?

813
00:47:30,582 --> 00:47:33,618
Today, it's Mika in charge. Part two!

814
00:47:34,352 --> 00:47:37,355
Bibbidi bobbidi boo!

815
00:47:37,422 --> 00:47:38,423
Whisky with water please.

816
00:47:50,635 --> 00:47:51,636
Goodbye.

817
00:47:53,271 --> 00:47:54,105
Ms. Sangenya!

818
00:48:00,078 --> 00:48:01,379
Do you have time?

819
00:48:02,180 --> 00:48:03,181
What is it?

820
00:48:05,316 --> 00:48:06,317
So?

821
00:48:09,020 --> 00:48:13,324
Lately, my nose has been bleeding a lot.

822
00:48:15,193 --> 00:48:16,661
In that case, go and see a doctor for it.

823
00:48:16,961 --> 00:48:20,565
It's not an illness. It happens when
I'm in a certain situation.

824
00:48:20,999 --> 00:48:22,433
What kind of a situation?

825
00:48:24,035 --> 00:48:25,036
It's…

826
00:48:29,707 --> 00:48:31,809
Don't ask me for advice
and keep me in suspense.

827
00:48:32,210 --> 00:48:34,345
I'm sorry. It's…

828
00:48:36,214 --> 00:48:38,616
I met someone I sort of like,

829
00:48:39,250 --> 00:48:41,252
and when that feeling becomes strong…

830
00:48:42,053 --> 00:48:45,923
That happens to everyone.
I've experienced it before.

831
00:48:46,157 --> 00:48:49,260
What? You've had a nose bleed before?

832
00:48:49,327 --> 00:48:50,328
Yes.

833
00:48:52,630 --> 00:48:56,367
My nose started to bleed after being
excited about the opposite sex.

834
00:48:57,268 --> 00:49:01,673
That's only when
it's the opposite sex, right?

835
00:49:02,607 --> 00:49:06,311
Whether it's an attraction between
a man and a woman

836
00:49:06,377 --> 00:49:08,413
or a woman and a woman or a man and a man,

837
00:49:08,846 --> 00:49:11,449
the mechanism that causes
a bloody nose is the same.

838
00:49:12,917 --> 00:49:15,320
So a nose bleed can't be helped?

839
00:49:15,853 --> 00:49:18,523
Once you get past that period
and your feeling stabilizes,

840
00:49:18,923 --> 00:49:20,258
your nose won't bleed.

841
00:49:21,826 --> 00:49:22,860
I see.

842
00:49:24,595 --> 00:49:25,797
Is that all?

843
00:49:26,431 --> 00:49:28,199
That's it. Thank you.

844
00:49:29,033 --> 00:49:30,034
See you.

845
00:49:39,944 --> 00:49:41,279
This is the next day.

846
00:49:41,713 --> 00:49:44,148
This is my birthday dinner.

847
00:49:46,751 --> 00:49:50,121
Manager. Are you happy,
or are you suffering?

848
00:49:51,322 --> 00:49:53,057
I wonder which.

849
00:49:53,591 --> 00:49:57,995
Sangenya's childhood was complicated,

850
00:49:58,062 --> 00:50:00,898
so she doesn't express herself well
and is very strange.

851
00:50:01,866 --> 00:50:05,837
She used to be homeless too.

852
00:50:12,443 --> 00:50:15,580
How come you know that?

853
00:50:26,491 --> 00:50:28,126
FRIED NOODLES

854
00:50:36,434 --> 00:50:37,568
I will sell it.

855
00:50:37,635 --> 00:50:39,370
-Call me Kyoko.
-LGBT?

856
00:50:39,437 --> 00:50:41,973
Are we supposed to be ashamed
of our relationship?

857
00:50:42,039 --> 00:50:43,241
You guys are gay too?

858
00:50:43,307 --> 00:50:46,177
You two are in love,
and that's all that matters.

859
00:50:46,244 --> 00:50:49,013
The lives of LGBT are just as precious.

860
00:50:49,080 --> 00:50:50,381
Don't you forget!

861
00:50:50,448 --> 00:50:51,282
THIS DRAMA IS A FICTION
